comments.message:
If you're referring to cper-json-bank0/1 in cper-memory and cper-memory2, they're the same object. Their parent $id can be used to identify them.

The point of this is to resolve collisions arising due to oneOf[] properties, where there may be duplicate properties under each oneOf[] object. In the nested scheme of things, there's no way to uniquely identify each "child" property. For example, validationBits in this case:

```
oneOf[
   {
    validationBits: {},
    abc: {}
   },
   {
    validationBits: {},
    xyz: {}
   }
]
```
